Name: mal de Meleda
Definition: A palmoplantar keratosis characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of symmetric palmoplantar hyperkeratosis that progressively extends to the dorsal surfaces of hands and feet and ichthyotic changes elsewhere that has material_basis_in  homozygous mutation in the SLURP1 gene on chromosome 8q24.

Name: epidermolytic palmoplantar keratoderma
Definition: A palmoplantar keratosis that is characterized by marked hyperkeratosis on the surface of palms and soles.
Synonym: Primary mediastinal clear cell lymphoma of B-cell type
